---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
const accountBaseUrl = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_ACCOUNT_URL || import.meta.env.PUBLIC_APP_URL || "http://localhost:3000";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="How DonateCrate Works"
  description="See how DonateCrate monthly donation pickup works, from address check to pickup day."
>
  <main class="simple-page">
    <a class="back-link" href="/">Back to home</a>
    <span class="eyebrow">How It Works</span>
    <h1>A monthly routine that feels much easier than making another drop-off trip.</h1>
    <p class="simple-page__lede">
      DonateCrate is built to make donating feel simple, predictable, and easy to keep up with. You check your
      address once, create your account, and then follow the same clear pickup rhythm each month.
    </p>
    <div class="simple-grid">
      <article>
        <h2>1. Confirm your address</h2>
        <p>Start with your street address so we can tell you whether signup is open now or whether your neighborhood is next.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>2. Create your account</h2>
        <p>Your address flows into signup, so you do not have to repeat the same details just to get started.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>3. Set out your bag monthly</h2>
        <p>When you are ready for the month, confirm your pickup in the app and place your bag out on the scheduled day.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
    <section class="feature-band">
      <article>
        <span class="eyebrow">Before pickup day</span>
        <h2>We help you stay on top of it.</h2>
        <p>You can see your current month, confirm if you are ready, and get reminders ahead of route day.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span class="eyebrow">As we grow</span>
        <h2>Neighborhood rollout stays intentional.</h2>
        <p>We expand carefully so pickups stay dependable and each new area gets a service experience worth using.</p>
      </article>
    </section>
    <a class="button" href="/signup">Start account setup</a>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
